quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  4,142,"The hypocrites seek to trick God, but God is tricking them. When they stand up to pray they stand up lazily, showing off to the people and not remembering God save a little"
  4,143,"wavering all the time -- not to these, not to those; and whom God leads astray, thou wilt not find for him a way"
  4,144,"O believers, take not the unbelievers as friends instead of the believers; or do you desire to give God over you a clear authority"
  4,145,Surely the hypocrites will be in the lowest reach of the Fire; thou wilt not find for them any helper
  4,146,"save such as repent, and make amends, and hold fast to God, and make their religion sincerely God's; those are with the believers, and God will certainly give the believers a mighty wage"
  4,147,"What would God do with chastising you if you are thankful, and believe? God is All-thankful, All-knowing"
  4,148,"God likes not the shouting of evil words unless a man has been wronged; God is All-hearing, All-knowing"
  4,149,"If you do good openly or in secret or pardon an evil, surely God is All-pardoning, All-powerful"
  4,150,"Those who disbelieve in God and His Messengers and desire to make division between God and His Messengers, and say, 'We believe in part, and disbelieve in part,' desiring to take between this and that a way"
  4,151,those in truth are the unbelievers; and We have prepared for the unbelievers a humbling chastisement
  4,152,"And those who believe in God and His Messengers and make no division between any of them, those -- We shall surely give them their wages; God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate"